author: eTN Global Editor
title: Fire on cruise ship totally extinguished
text:
Fire on cruise ship totally extinguished Adv: 
Jul 22, 2015 Adv: 
KINGSTON, Jamaica - Cruise shipping activities are proceeding as usual at the Falmouth cruise ship pier in Trelawny as a fire, which occurred on the Freedom of the Seas vessel, was extinguished by the ship's crew. 
Minister of Tourism and Entertainment, Hon. Dr. Wykeham McNeill stated that "the team on the ship were able to extinguish the blaze. We are currently in contact with our partners and the owners of the vessel and are keeping abreast of the situation." 
The Minister added that “the fire was not very big and none of the visitors had to be evacuated. We sincerely hope the visitors will enjoy the rest of their stay.”
